  "texts": [
    "38 It is interesting that we needed exactly n + 2g -2 of the b(µ I) insertions for a nonanomalous radial translation.",
    "We mentioned in section 3.3 that we should include this number of b(µ I) insertions to cancel the anomalies of the ghost currents of the hybrid formalism (this is shown in detail in appendix B).",
    "It appears that the background charge of Φ is therefore related to that of the ρ ghost.To reiterate, the global radial symmetry has been derived here using consistency arguments for the existence of spurious poles in the correlation function.",
    "To be more precise as to how these poles can actually occur, notice that the insertions δ(S) (2.26) have the required properties to account for these spurious poles.",
    "In particular, correlation functions (2.28) of highest weight states are of the formC g (x, w) = n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) M a=1 δ S a.We therefore need to consider how the δ(S) change under K. Let the contour C in (2.26) be a small contour around the origin."
